{
  "texts": [
    "[49] 2020 Question Answering \"AI hallucination\" refers to the occurrence when AI generates content inconsistent with the source document, i.e., unfaithful. 14 Zhao et al.",
    "[28] 2020 Text Summarization \"AI hallucination\" occurs when language models generate material that is not supported by the original text. 15 Dong et al.",
    "[29] 2020 Text Summarization \"AI hallucination\" occurs when a language model generates content that is factually inconsistent with the source documents.",
    "16 Filippova [8] 2020 Large Language Model \"AI hallucination\" refers to the generated content which is either unfaithful to the input or nonsensical. 17 Zhou et al.",
    "[50] 2020 Hallucination Detection \"AI hallucination\" occurs when the model generates additional content not supported by the input. 18 Elsahar et al."
  ]
}